bug.short_desc: Download stats do not show for all drivers.

long_desc.thetext:
Download stats do not show for all drivers.
For example, they appear for the 4.4.1 candidate build but not the 4.5 M3 stable build (see attached).
Deferral to future with PMC approval

Created attachment 102218 Patch removing flock commands from generateStatistics and fetchStatistics
Download stats would always appear on another webserver but the flock command behaves differently with certain Linux servers so I remover it from the code.
Created attachment 105891 Updated patch removing flock

I cannot verify this defect until we have some 4.5.1 builds since the 4.5 builds have been removed now that 4.5 is GA.
Joel, the stats for the existing releases are somewhat old (e.g. Oct 2007 for 4.4.0.2 and June 11 for 4.5.0). Is this a known issue?

Download stats are only for drivers that are mirrored and not archived (which would include any driver that is not the current release, maintenance release or a candidate).
The current driver having old stats is something I have been tracking. I had already contacted the webmasters and am still waiting on follow up.
Reopening since the TPTP 4.5.0 stats are all at 0.
Reassigning to webmaster as we are still waiting on response from them for questions about this.
The webmasters have provided a patch.

Paul, Can you please verify the fix?
Thanks

The 4.5.0 stats look good. Thanks.
The stats for the existing releases are still somewhat old (e.g. Oct 2007 for 4.4.0.2).
Also, are we tracking stats for current releases (e.g. 4.5.1)?

From Comment #7: Download stats are only for drivers that are mirrored and not archived (which would include any driver that is not the current release, maintenance release or a candidate).
We will track stats for 4.5.1 when a driver is promoted.
